# Project Rules

## Tech Stack
[TODO: Update for this project]

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- No `any` types — use `unknown` or proper generics
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`
- Use `async`/`await` over raw promises
- Use named exports (avoid default exports)
- Descriptive variable names — no abbreviations

## File Organization
- One class per file
- PascalCase for class/component files
- camelCase for utility/helper files
- Keep files under 200 lines; split if larger

## Git Conventions
- Imperative present tense commit messages ("add feature" not "added feature")
- One logical change per commit

## Error Handling
- Handle fetch failures gracefully with user-friendly error states
- Use circuit breaker pattern for external API calls
- Never swallow errors silently

## Comments
- Comment the *why*, not the *what*
- No commented-out code in commits
- JSDoc for all exported functions and types
